KESTER: Being brave isn't
about never being afraid.

18:56.490 --> 19:00.490
It's about what you do when you are.

19:01.250 --> 19:03.890
Whether you can keep your head.
Whether you do the right thing.

19:03.890 --> 19:06.170
In the spring,

19:06.170 --> 19:09.690
I was admitted to a mental home,

19:09.690 --> 19:12.690
because I kept trying to hurt myself.

19:12.690 --> 19:15.930
KESTER: If I was to ask one of your
friends what they liked about you,

19:15.930 --> 19:18.730
- what do you think they would say?
- FINN: Our group of friends was...

19:18.730 --> 19:20.850
was nothing until you
sprayed Rae all over it.

19:20.850 --> 19:23.610
You're the one they always look to.

19:23.610 --> 19:24.850
You're the glue.

19:24.850 --> 19:28.210
KESTER: You see yourself
as a fragile thing,

19:28.210 --> 19:32.210
like a little broken bird,
sloshing around in a bottle.

19:32.850 --> 19:36.450
But, basically, I think
you're a pretty tough cookie.

19:36.450 --> 19:39.610
You don't think that people can change.

19:39.610 --> 19:43.610
But I know that they can.

19:44.130 --> 19:45.850
<i>If I really was a voodoo doll,
</i>

19:45.850 --> 19:47.890
<i>causing all that pain,
</i>

19:47.890 --> 19:51.890
<i>then it was only because I'd
been sticking the pins in myself.
</i>

19:52.650 --> 19:54.610
<i>And if I'd stuck them in...
</i>

19:54.610 --> 19:58.610
<i>then I could pull them out again.
</i>

20:00.250 --> 20:01.770
How are the hands?

20:01.770 --> 20:04.010
A bit better.

20:04.010 --> 20:07.530
Good.

20:07.530 --> 20:10.570
So, without wishing to sound rude, Rachel,

20:10.570 --> 20:12.970
why are you here?

20:12.970 --> 20:14.850
Well...

20:14.850 --> 20:17.690
I need your help.

20:17.690 --> 20:19.730
I wanna go to Bristol.

20:19.730 --> 20:23.530
Decided I can do it.

20:23.530 --> 20:27.530
So, I was wondering if you would
be able to write me a letter,

20:28.130 --> 20:30.570
in case I don't get the grades.

20:30.570 --> 20:33.170
Saying what?

20:33.170 --> 20:37.170
Just saying that I would've got the
grades if I hadn't have been in here.

20:37.930 --> 20:40.210
I can write a letter,

20:40.210 --> 20:44.210
but I'm afraid I've no idea
what grades you would've got.

20:44.770 --> 20:47.330
Why the sudden turnaround?

20:47.330 --> 20:50.290
You seem so certain about things.

20:50.290 --> 20:52.330
But not so long ago,
you were just as certain

20:52.330 --> 20:55.050
you couldn't manage any of this.

20:55.050 --> 20:57.010
Kester says...

20:57.010 --> 20:59.410
that I owe it to myself to try.

20:59.410 --> 21:01.890
How are you going to do that?

21:01.890 --> 21:04.290
Well...

21:04.290 --> 21:08.130
... I've just gotta learn
how to handle things...

21:08.130 --> 21:12.130
on my own.

21:14.690 --> 21:18.690
I'm gonna stop waiting for
someone to come and save me.

21:18.930 --> 21:22.930
So, do you need this letter?

21:24.290 --> 21:26.210
No.

21:26.210 --> 21:30.210
What does that mean?

21:30.650 --> 21:34.010
I guess it means...

21:34.010 --> 21:37.930
... that we're done.

21:37.930 --> 21:40.330
No offence.

21:40.330 --> 21:43.210
I'm glad to hear it.

21:43.210 --> 21:47.210
No offence.

21:53.570 --> 21:57.570
MUSIC: The Medication
Is Wearing Off by Eels

22:01.290 --> 22:04.210
Performing Arts Theory is two hours long.

22:04.210 --> 22:08.210
It's also, for many of you,
your final exam, so good luck.

22:08.850 --> 22:11.490
Time now is two o'clock, which
gives you until four o'clock.

22:11.490 --> 22:15.490
You may turn over your papers.

22:16.370 --> 22:18.010
<i>I'd missed one exam already.
</i>

22:18.010 --> 22:21.130
<i>That meant this one
mattered more than ever.
</i>

22:21.130 --> 22:23.130
<i>I had to make up the marks.
</i>

22:23.130 --> 22:27.130
<i>I didn't know if I'd pass or
fail, let alone get into Bristol.
</i>

22:27.330 --> 22:29.810
<i>I just knew I had to try.
</i>

22:29.810 --> 22:32.050
<i>Bit by bit, question by question,
</i>

22:32.050 --> 22:34.490
<i>for no-one else other than me.
</i>

22:34.490 --> 22:38.490
♪ ... The days I'm
claiming back for me... ♪

22:40.090 --> 22:41.770
BELL RINGS

22:41.770 --> 22:45.770
♪ ... Doo-doo doo dooo ♪
♪ Doo-doo doo-doo dooo dooo... ♪

22:48.330 --> 22:50.850
<i>But just because my exams were over
</i>

22:50.850 --> 22:53.330
<i>didn't mean my problems suddenly were.
</i>

22:53.330 --> 22:55.930
<i>And some things will never let you go.
</i>

22:55.930 --> 22:59.930
<i>Not until you find the
strength to deal with them.
</i>

23:00.770 --> 23:04.770
<i>It was time to tell the gang about Finn.
</i>

23:06.610 --> 23:08.250
- No fucking way.
- That's what she told me.

23:08.250 --> 23:10.090
- Are you serious, Rae?
- That's disgusting.

23:10.090 --> 23:14.090
Guys... Guys... before you kick
off, just hear me out, yeah?

23:15.130 --> 23:18.530
I haven't been easy to
go out with. Trust me.

23:18.530 --> 23:20.930
He's meant to be your
plus-one for the leavers' ball.

23:20.930 --> 23:23.650
He's supposed to be a
plus-one for longer than that.

23:23.650 --> 23:27.010
Forget about Finn. Are you all right, Rae?

23:27.010 --> 23:29.610
Yeah, we've been worried about you.

23:29.610 --> 23:30.850
Well...

23:30.850 --> 23:34.810
that's why I wanted us to get together.

23:34.810 --> 23:37.850
So I can explain why
I've been feeling the way

23:37.850 --> 23:41.090
that I've been feeling.

23:41.090 --> 23:45.090
OK, the only way that
I can describe it is...

23:45.370 --> 23:49.370
... it's like I'm walking
through a forest the whole time

23:49.930 --> 23:51.770
and, for the most part...

23:51.770 --> 23:54.170
it's fine.

23:54.170 --> 23:55.530
It can...

23:55.530 --> 23:58.410
be beautiful.

23:58.410 --> 24:00.810
Peaceful, even.

24:00.810 --> 24:02.530
But...

24:02.530 --> 24:05.930
you always know that at some point...

24:05.930 --> 24:08.970
... you're gonna come across
these parts of the forest

24:08.970 --> 24:11.770
that you don't recognise.

24:11.770 --> 24:15.530
Dark corners that you didn't
know were there, but...

24:15.530 --> 24:17.850
well, you always kind
of knew they were coming.

24:17.850 --> 24:21.850
- Does that make sense?
- Yeah.

24:22.970 --> 24:26.970
And that's when the world gets scary.

24:28.290 --> 24:31.970
And that's when you can lose your way.

24:31.970 --> 24:33.970
But...

24:33.970 --> 24:37.930
because I've got great mates...

24:37.930 --> 24:41.930
and people who make me
strong and remind me that...

24:43.450 --> 24:47.450
well, even when I hit those
dark parts of the forest...

24:48.370 --> 24:49.610
... that...

24:49.610 --> 24:51.810
I've just gotta keep walking.

24:51.810 --> 24:55.810
Just keep walking, and I'll be OK.

24:56.570 --> 25:00.050
I'll be scared.

25:00.050 --> 25:01.850
But I'll be OK.

25:01.850 --> 25:03.610
So...

25:03.610 --> 25:07.610
you have to promise me
that you're not gonna worry.

25:09.170 --> 25:12.330
And you're not going to hate Finn. Promise?

25:12.330 --> 25:13.650
- Promise.
- Promise?

25:13.650 --> 25:14.850
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

25:14.850 --> 25:17.290
It's OK to hate Katie
Springer, though, right?

25:17.290 --> 25:20.210
- Yeah.
- Definitely.

25:20.210 --> 25:24.210
You're not talking about the
woods in Burghley Park, are you?

25:25.730 --> 25:27.570
What?

25:27.570 --> 25:29.570
I go there on my bike all the time.

25:29.570 --> 25:31.650
LAUGHTER

25:31.650 --> 25:33.330
There's loads of dark pa...

25:33.330 --> 25:35.990
You should cycle somewhere
else, genius that you are.

25:40.592 --> 25:41.632
Rae!

25:41.632 --> 25:42.752
Rae.

25:42.752 --> 25:44.192
Look, I just wanted to say,

25:44.192 --> 25:46.752
if Finn doesn't take
you to the leavers' ball,

25:46.752 --> 25:50.752
then I'd consider it an honour
to step in and take you myself.

25:51.952 --> 25:53.792
The only possible caveat

25:53.792 --> 25:56.632
is that I've made some inroads with Kelly

25:56.632 --> 25:58.912
who does the trolleys in
the Safeway's car park.

25:58.912 --> 26:01.032
So if she pages me back...

26:01.032 --> 26:03.312
I'd have to renege on my offer.

26:03.312 --> 26:05.552
I mean, I can't have blurred lines, Rae.

26:05.552 --> 26:06.992
Understood.

26:06.992 --> 26:08.312
Thanks, Danny.

26:08.312 --> 26:10.392
- Chlo...
- I told her, Rae.

26:10.392 --> 26:13.032
I warned her.

26:13.032 --> 26:15.392
Shit. Chlo!

26:15.392 --> 26:18.512
Chlo, wait up. Chlo!

26:18.512 --> 26:21.592
- Chloe...
- What car is it?

26:21.592 --> 26:23.792
Is it one of these?

26:23.792 --> 26:25.912
Or is it this one?

26:25.912 --> 26:29.272
- It's this one, isn't it?
- Chlo...

26:29.272 --> 26:33.272
♪ That girl think she's the
queen of the neighbourhood ♪

26:33.272 --> 26:36.432
♪ She got the hottest trike in town... ♪

26:36.432 --> 26:37.552
RAE MOUTHS

26:37.552 --> 26:39.552
♪ That girl she holds her head up so high ♪

26:39.552 --> 26:41.472
♪ I think I wanna be her
best friend, yeah... ♪

26:41.472 --> 26:44.712
Chloe!

26:44.712 --> 26:47.192
Chloe, you've just got out of hospital.

26:47.192 --> 26:49.872
KATIE: What's she doing?

26:49.872 --> 26:51.032
Chloe?

26:51.032 --> 26:52.752
I told you, Katie.

26:52.752 --> 26:54.632
I warned you.

26:54.632 --> 26:56.392
- What are you doing?
- I warned you.

26:56.392 --> 27:00.272
You mess with my best
mate, this is what happens.

27:00.272 --> 27:04.152
Your shitty little car gets it.

27:04.152 --> 27:07.912
Chloe, that's not my car.

27:07.912 --> 27:08.952
That's my car.

27:08.952 --> 27:12.952
GUITAR RIFF

27:19.472 --> 27:23.112
- Oi, Katie.
- No, I get it, Rae, OK?

27:23.112 --> 27:25.272
Yeah, I get it, your mate's pissed off.

27:25.272 --> 27:26.712
Can we just drop it, please?

27:26.712 --> 27:28.672
Yeah, OK, yeah, we can.

27:28.672 --> 27:31.472
But this is the last
time that we ever speak,

27:31.472 --> 27:32.912
even if I get into uni.

27:32.912 --> 27:34.912
You're gonna to go to Bristol

27:34.912 --> 27:37.192
and you're gonna ignore the
only person that you know?

27:37.192 --> 27:39.912
Yeah. Yeah, I am, Katie.

27:39.912 --> 27:42.672
Because there is no way you
are anything like a proper mate,

27:42.672 --> 27:44.432
and if your life was so amazing,

27:44.432 --> 27:47.512
then you wouldn't be hanging
around in a Lincolnshire cul-de-sac

27:47.512 --> 27:51.512
with the girls from the
year below, would you?

27:56.472 --> 27:58.032
Chlo...

27:58.032 --> 27:59.632
OK?

27:59.632 --> 28:03.632
Listen, you do know that you doing
that makes me love you even more?

28:03.952 --> 28:07.952
Even more than if you'd
have got the right car.

28:08.592 --> 28:12.512
What made you go for the bins?

28:12.512 --> 28:15.832
The only thing I could think of!

28:15.832 --> 28:18.152
Chlo, can you do me a favour?

28:18.152 --> 28:22.152
Will you please try and
stop worrying about me?

28:22.152 --> 28:24.472
I know it's hard, because I am literally

28:24.472 --> 28:27.392
the easiest person in the
world to worry about, but...

28:27.392 --> 28:29.352
You've gotta try.

28:29.352 --> 28:31.232
Yeah?

28:31.232 --> 28:32.512
Yeah.

28:32.512 --> 28:35.472
Got bin juice on my hand now.

28:35.472 --> 28:37.152
- Whose car is that?
- I don't know,

28:37.152 --> 28:39.192
but they're gonna be well pissed.

28:39.192 --> 28:41.152
Come on, hurry up!

28:41.152 --> 28:44.552
BOTH GIGGLE

28:44.552 --> 28:48.392
GIGGLING CONTINUES

28:48.392 --> 28:50.392
A bit racy.

28:50.392 --> 28:52.232
Racy?

28:52.232 --> 28:53.792
Yeah.

28:53.792 --> 28:55.632
Well, racy.

28:55.632 --> 28:57.512
As in... racy.

28:57.512 --> 29:00.312
Oh, OK. Perfect.

29:00.312 --> 29:04.312
That's the look I normally go for.

29:07.712 --> 29:10.672
Oh!

29:10.672 --> 29:13.432
- OK.
- Oh, good.

29:13.432 --> 29:17.432
- Here you are, then.
- Thanks.

29:18.472 --> 29:22.272
<i>The leavers' ball wasn't
exactly top of my to-do list,
</i>

29:22.272 --> 29:25.752
<i>especially without Finn...
</i>

29:25.752 --> 29:27.352
Any good?

29:27.352 --> 29:31.312
<i>... but I had to show
Mum I was on the mend.
</i>

29:31.312 --> 29:32.992
Bought it when I was 30.

29:32.992 --> 29:36.352
When I was, and don't bite my head off,

29:36.352 --> 29:39.032
I was a couple of sizes bigger.

29:39.032 --> 29:43.032
I never... quite had the
confidence to wear it out.

29:53.472 --> 29:56.352
Oh, Rae.

29:56.352 --> 29:58.752
I'll wear it.

29:58.752 --> 30:01.432
On one condition.

30:01.432 --> 30:05.112
You go to Tunisia.

30:05.112 --> 30:06.792
- No.
- Mum...

30:06.792 --> 30:10.352
Karim will be missing you like crazy.

30:10.352 --> 30:12.272
You're his life.

30:12.272 --> 30:15.592
I will ring you constantly.

30:15.592 --> 30:19.352
There's this thing called
e-mail. Everyone's getting them.

30:19.352 --> 30:21.752
It's not about that.

30:21.752 --> 30:23.832
Mum...

30:23.832 --> 30:26.072
They still look sore.

30:26.072 --> 30:29.792
Yeah. They are.

30:29.792 --> 30:32.232
But they'll heal.

30:32.232 --> 30:34.912
I am learning how to handle things.

30:34.912 --> 30:38.912
But how am I gonna know you're OK?

30:39.592 --> 30:43.592
You don't.

30:45.152 --> 30:49.152
I'd have to hand my notice
in at the hospital...

30:56.272 --> 31:00.272
RAE SIGHS

31:03.272 --> 31:04.952
Do you need a little jacket?

31:04.952 --> 31:08.952
- How about a little jacket?
- Mum...

31:09.072 --> 31:13.072
I've got a jacket.

31:21.632 --> 31:25.632
KNOCK ON DOOR

31:26.552 --> 31:28.592
You look lovely.

31:28.592 --> 31:31.432
So do you.

31:31.432 --> 31:35.432
You just look a bit more
pyjama-y than I expected.

31:38.312 --> 31:41.152
I can't face it, Rae.

31:41.152 --> 31:44.392
What are you on about?

31:44.392 --> 31:47.232
Well... CHLOE SNIFFS

31:47.232 --> 31:48.832
W...

31:48.832 --> 31:50.832
Well, what happens next?

31:50.832 --> 31:53.152
Business college.

31:53.152 --> 31:57.152
I don't know. I don't...

31:58.272 --> 32:02.272
I only got that because my dad
plays golf with the guy who runs it.

32:02.632 --> 32:05.032
And if I don't do that, then...

32:05.032 --> 32:09.032
then I don't know what I'm gonna do.

32:11.752 --> 32:15.312
I just know that I won't
get to do it with you.

32:15.312 --> 32:19.312
Chlo...

32:20.032 --> 32:24.032
Like... when you told me
to stop worrying about you.

32:25.712 --> 32:28.112
Well, I knew then that you were leaving.

32:28.112 --> 32:29.712
Yeah.

32:29.712 --> 32:33.712
Everyone's leaving, aren't they?

32:35.632 --> 32:39.632
The gang'll stay in
touch, for a bit, but...

32:39.632 --> 32:43.632
Well...

32:45.832 --> 32:49.832
It's just life, isn't it?

32:51.352 --> 32:55.312
But me and you, right...

32:55.312 --> 32:57.432
... we are Chloe and Rae.

32:57.432 --> 33:01.192
We're not the gang.

33:01.192 --> 33:03.872
And if I go to Bristol...

33:03.872 --> 33:05.832
... then you can just come and visit.

33:05.832 --> 33:08.072
Yeah?

33:08.072 --> 33:10.272
Yeah, that'll be good.

33:10.272 --> 33:14.272
It doesn't matter where we
are or what we're doing...

33:14.392 --> 33:18.392
... I promise we are always
gonna be Chloe and Rae.

33:18.632 --> 33:21.832
Yeah?

33:21.832 --> 33:23.072
Yeah.

33:23.072 --> 33:26.592
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

33:26.592 --> 33:28.392
Chloe...

33:28.392 --> 33:29.752
What?

33:29.752 --> 33:33.752
I spent ages on this make-up
and you've made me cry!

33:34.312 --> 33:36.232
No, you made me cry!

33:36.232 --> 33:38.592
No, I was fine. It was you.

33:38.592 --> 33:40.512
Are you gonna go get ready, then?

33:40.512 --> 33:42.112
Yeah.

33:42.112 --> 33:44.712
And can I borrow some
eyeliner or something?

33:44.712 --> 33:48.712
- Yeah, I'll do your make-up.
- Thank you.

33:49.872 --> 33:52.232
Izzy, what's happened to your arm?

33:52.232 --> 33:54.912
Oh, it's better now. I'll
take it off in a minute.

33:54.912 --> 33:57.192
It clashes with my dress.

33:57.192 --> 34:01.192
Here he is.

34:01.472 --> 34:04.632
My date.

34:04.632 --> 34:07.352
- You all look gorgeous.
- Hello!

34:07.352 --> 34:09.232
Mwah!

34:09.232 --> 34:11.911
Look at him. He's total lush.

34:11.911 --> 34:13.911
Hurry up, knobhead.

34:13.911 --> 34:16.152
Right, let's do this.

34:16.152 --> 34:17.752
Er, wait.

34:17.752 --> 34:20.792
Er, I know things have
been a bit tricky lately,

34:20.792 --> 34:24.351
um... but he wanted me to ask, so...

34:24.351 --> 34:27.992
Uh, if Finn and you may be able
to be mates in the future...

34:27.992 --> 34:30.232
Archie, can we not do this now, please?

34:30.232 --> 34:32.672
To be honest, Raemundo, he
kind of needs to know now.

34:32.672 --> 34:35.911
Cab's cost him a right fortune.

34:35.911 --> 34:38.752
CAR DOOR SHUTS

34:38.752 --> 34:42.752
MUSIC: Careless Whisper by Wham!

34:42.753 --> 34:47.065
_

34:48.952 --> 34:51.831
<i>Finn Nelson... late, not invited,
</i>

34:51.831 --> 34:55.472
<i>taking his life in his own
hands just by being here
</i>

34:55.472 --> 34:57.672
<i>and looking beyond sexy in a tuxedo,
</i>

34:57.672 --> 35:01.672
<i>which, Dear Diary, is not the point.
</i>

35:05.512 --> 35:07.992
- CHOP: Izzy!
- Sorry.

35:07.992 --> 35:11.992
Archie!

35:13.352 --> 35:14.592
<i>Well, this was awkward.
</i>

35:15.712 --> 35:19.152
MUSIC: Never Ever by All Saints

35:19.152 --> 35:21.152
SHE SIGHS

35:21.152 --> 35:25.152
- Rae, I, um... I... I kissed Katie...
- Finn... It's fine.

35:25.592 --> 35:28.032
No, it's not.

35:28.032 --> 35:31.712
I hurt you, and...

35:31.712 --> 35:35.192
... I'm sorry.

35:35.192 --> 35:37.472
You spend all this time saying how...

35:37.472 --> 35:41.472
how you're not good enough for me,
but I'm not good enough for you.

35:43.192 --> 35:46.432
I'm no better than any of the other
19-year-old knobheads out there.

35:46.432 --> 35:49.312
Are you criticising my
taste in men now, or what?

35:49.312 --> 35:52.212
I'm serious, Rae.

35:53.312 --> 35:55.212
I let you down.

35:55.312 --> 35:59.032
Listen...

35:59.032 --> 36:03.032
... I shouldn't have made
out that you were Mr Perfect.

36:04.792 --> 36:07.572
It wasn't fair.

36:08.272 --> 36:11.232
But me and you...

36:11.232 --> 36:15.232
... we're going to be all right.

36:15.872 --> 36:19.872
And you know why, don't you?

36:19.992 --> 36:22.792
Cos me and you, we...

36:22.792 --> 36:26.792
... we don't always have to be an "us".

36:27.232 --> 36:30.472
And just because we're not
together now, Finn Nelson...

36:30.472 --> 36:33.632
doesn't mean that we'll never be.

36:33.632 --> 36:34.912
OK?

36:34.912 --> 36:38.752
Yeah.

36:38.752 --> 36:42.632
If it all goes tits-up in Bristol...

